<subSubSection id="861042A9C0B14C9A37D2A245B1ACF818" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648" type="description">
<paragraph id="B10337AF7826CE993CCD55A42CB0BCB2" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E71DD376D9A4A7B164022A062C8747EE" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">
Saprobic on dead aboveground stem of 
<taxonomicName id="FDDAE2AEC9BBD478E56BE96F4AED69ED" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Heracleum" higherTaxonomySource="IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heracleum sphondylium" order="Apiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="sphondylium">
<emphasis id="B1B94C5DDA394F456EE63C0DADBAEDF6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">Heracleum sphondylium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName id="DE437A4A1C9DA9A2AEEF46D9C4C973B5" authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Heracleum" higherTaxonomySource="IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Apiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="order">Apiales</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A720632EC16CBB86763845DAAB54465C" authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Heracleum" higherTaxonomySource="IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Apiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="family">Apiaceae</taxonomicName>
). 
<emphasis id="9160792D7EFB1D2690396C844DE4DBC3" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">Sexual morph</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="0EFEFCCD3C645BF021A29BDA0498515A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">Ascomata</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AE7BCF05044DF9312DE01F1086920B43" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F6199310" captionText="Figure 3. Italica heraclei (MFLU 18 - 1906). a-b. Ascomata on a dead stem of Heracleum sphondylium (Apiales, Apiaceae). c. Section of an ascoma. d. Peridium. e. Pseudoparaphyses. f-j. Asci. k-n. Ascospores. o-p. Colonies on PDA from upper (o) and lower (p) sides. Scale bars: a-b = 200 µm, c = 100 µm, d-j = 20 µm, k-n = 10 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e59648.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/479944" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">3</figureCitation>
a-c) 250-280 
<normalizedToken id="247016A9A0492F253A68D602BA12C13F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
230-250 
<normalizedToken id="98A2961E4284A1A15C6A03C21D666822" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(x¯ = 257 
<normalizedToken id="924FECEC601AEC051E9A7F2DE645001E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
237 
<normalizedToken id="4E6F826C9D093F66AAEF95ECEEC6D3B2" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, n = 10), immersed to erumpent, solitary scattered, sessile, globose to subglobose, uniloculate, dark brown to black, coriaceous, ostiolate. 
<emphasis id="6ACACC98F7ACE51C423024E163F34217" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">Ostiole</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E5431EACB8C0BA601D4DAEBBD189C7F0" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F6199310" captionText="Figure 3. Italica heraclei (MFLU 18 - 1906). a-b. Ascomata on a dead stem of Heracleum sphondylium (Apiales, Apiaceae). c. Section of an ascoma. d. Peridium. e. Pseudoparaphyses. f-j. Asci. k-n. Ascospores. o-p. Colonies on PDA from upper (o) and lower (p) sides. Scale bars: a-b = 200 µm, c = 100 µm, d-j = 20 µm, k-n = 10 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e59648.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/479944" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">3</figureCitation>
c) papillate, 70-85 
<normalizedToken id="024651FF7052C59EB0837AE4781E35A4" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
long, 80-100 
<normalizedToken id="02445651D0B55373C972883547DBBDD9" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide, central, comprising blackish-brown to pale brown or hyaline cells. 
<emphasis id="851F9D1FE4BD544DD7A54A64307BB855" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">Peridium</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="042FE3B2387888B31295C1F2B16BB285" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F6199310" captionText="Figure 3. Italica heraclei (MFLU 18 - 1906). a-b. Ascomata on a dead stem of Heracleum sphondylium (Apiales, Apiaceae). c. Section of an ascoma. d. Peridium. e. Pseudoparaphyses. f-j. Asci. k-n. Ascospores. o-p. Colonies on PDA from upper (o) and lower (p) sides. Scale bars: a-b = 200 µm, c = 100 µm, d-j = 20 µm, k-n = 10 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e59648.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/479944" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">3</figureCitation>
d) 10-25 
<normalizedToken id="8F0E51FD8B706B71106D8476029156CF" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(x¯ = 16 
<normalizedToken id="38B325E01D24F07F8CCB9D97C3B51A09" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, n = 15) wide, thin-walled, composed of 4-6 cell layers, outermost layers heavily pigmented, comprising dark brown to pale brown cells of 
<emphasis id="5B38BF9CA46AFBD2BB92FDC7031D678D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">textura angularis</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="3F5B094105A3BCE3E372666441D341DA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">Hamathecium</emphasis>
comprising numerous, 2-3 
<normalizedToken id="FF65EB910E41F79486E3F6066F94CDCD" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide (x¯ = 2.5 
<normalizedToken id="382E98C8E580000B69F4D2FA21AFF2E3" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, n = 10), filamentous, branched pseudoparaphyses (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="496EF411928BDA1A45332E4009D3304C" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F6199310" captionText="Figure 3. Italica heraclei (MFLU 18 - 1906). a-b. Ascomata on a dead stem of Heracleum sphondylium (Apiales, Apiaceae). c. Section of an ascoma. d. Peridium. e. Pseudoparaphyses. f-j. Asci. k-n. Ascospores. o-p. Colonies on PDA from upper (o) and lower (p) sides. Scale bars: a-b = 200 µm, c = 100 µm, d-j = 20 µm, k-n = 10 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e59648.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/479944" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">3</figureCitation>
e) with distinct septa. 
<emphasis id="6F405CC84B8963215AF10DFDA4E42AD6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">Asci</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="AE1EA4A4E8E161744AF827A2C7A0DB4C" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F6199310" captionText="Figure 3. Italica heraclei (MFLU 18 - 1906). a-b. Ascomata on a dead stem of Heracleum sphondylium (Apiales, Apiaceae). c. Section of an ascoma. d. Peridium. e. Pseudoparaphyses. f-j. Asci. k-n. Ascospores. o-p. Colonies on PDA from upper (o) and lower (p) sides. Scale bars: a-b = 200 µm, c = 100 µm, d-j = 20 µm, k-n = 10 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e59648.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/479944" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">3</figureCitation>
f-k) 80-120 
<normalizedToken id="C37806B2BC577A7493ECB50166EFB55A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
8-9 
