(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="64D1E7179745EC94CB7B75870B21098E" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F6199310" captionText="Figure 3. Italica heraclei (MFLU 18 - 1906). a-b. Ascomata on a dead stem of Heracleum sphondylium (Apiales, Apiaceae). c. Section of an ascoma. d. Peridium. e. Pseudoparaphyses. f-j. Asci. k-n. Ascospores. o-p. Colonies on PDA from upper (o) and lower (p) sides. Scale bars: a-b = 200 µm, c = 100 µm, d-j = 20 µm, k-n = 10 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e59648.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/479944" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">3</figureCitation>
