<paragraph id="8E90156DCE3298D302E92BE3E8AEA27B" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">
Culture characteristics: Ascospores germinating on MEA (malt extract agar) within 2 days, from single-spore isolation. Colonies (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3DAEC0CBD315291467203F7CFCA6312E" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F6199310" captionText="Figure 3. Italica heraclei (MFLU 18 - 1906). a-b. Ascomata on a dead stem of Heracleum sphondylium (Apiales, Apiaceae). c. Section of an ascoma. d. Peridium. e. Pseudoparaphyses. f-j. Asci. k-n. Ascospores. o-p. Colonies on PDA from upper (o) and lower (p) sides. Scale bars: a-b = 200 µm, c = 100 µm, d-j = 20 µm, k-n = 10 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.9.e59648.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/479944" pageId="0" pageNumber="59648">3</figureCitation>
o-p) on PDA reaching 5-10 mm diam. after 28 days at 18°C, circular, entire edge, flat, dense, bright yellow in both upper and lower sides.
</paragraph>
